00:00:28,766 --> 00:00:30,166
Makes it a lot cleaner.

11
00:00:30,200 --> 00:00:31,000
-Quiet.

12
00:00:31,033 --> 00:00:32,000
The guard's coming this way.

13
00:00:32,033 --> 00:00:32,600
-Keep it down.

14
00:00:32,633 --> 00:00:33,400
All of you.

15
00:00:33,433 --> 00:00:35,133
-I had a bad dream.

16
00:00:35,166 --> 00:00:37,666
-Shut up and sleep.

17
00:00:37,700 --> 00:00:40,800
INMATE: Someday, I'll put
him to sleep permanently.

18
00:00:50,633 --> 00:00:52,566
[scream]

19
00:00:52,600 --> 00:00:53,533
-What the hell.

20
00:00:53,566 --> 00:00:55,666
I thought I told
you guys to shut up.

21
00:01:00,166 --> 00:01:03,633
[theme music]

22
00:02:34,615 --> 00:02:35,348
PHOTOGRAPHER: Yes.

23
00:02:35,382 --> 00:02:35,982
Nice.

24
00:02:36,015 --> 00:02:36,467
Now we're talking.

25
00:02:36,467 --> 00:02:37,287
OK.

26
00:02:37,287 --> 00:02:38,148
Do that thing with
your hair that you do.

27
00:02:38,148 --> 00:02:38,910
Oh, fierce.

28
00:02:38,910 --> 00:02:39,376
Whoa.

29
00:02:39,410 --> 00:02:40,410
OK.

30
00:02:40,443 --> 00:02:41,576
Now, look at me, but
don't look at me.

31
00:02:41,610 --> 00:02:42,310
That's it.

32
00:02:42,343 --> 00:02:43,343
Use that emotion.

33
00:02:43,376 --> 00:02:44,076
Love it.

34
00:02:44,110 --> 00:02:45,110
Good.

35
00:02:45,143 --> 00:02:46,876
Ah, this issue is going
to sell like crazy.

36
00:02:46,910 --> 00:02:48,043
You are a phenom.

37
00:02:48,076 --> 00:02:48,976
My best work yet.

38
00:02:53,476 --> 00:02:55,076
-He's so hot.

39
00:02:55,110 --> 00:02:57,776
-We'll just be focusing
on Barnaby today.

40
00:02:57,810 --> 00:02:59,510
Don't worry about the other one.

41
00:02:59,543 --> 00:02:59,984
PHOTOGRAPHER: Right.

42
00:03:00,017 --> 00:03:01,051
Got it.

43
00:03:01,084 --> 00:03:02,951
BARNABY: Ah, don't
leave the old man out.

44
00:03:02,984 --> 00:03:03,984
You'll hurt his feelings.

45
00:03:15,017 --> 00:03:15,684
-That's it.

46
00:03:15,717 --> 00:03:16,317
There go.

47
00:03:16,351 --> 00:03:16,951
Oh yeah.

48
00:03:16,984 --> 00:03:17,517
Very nice.

49
00:03:17,551 --> 00:03:20,851
Very, very nice.

50
00:03:20,884 --> 00:03:23,451
[chuckling]

51
00:03:23,484 --> 00:03:23,951
-Yes.

52
00:03:23,984 --> 00:03:24,584
Yes.

53
00:03:24,617 --> 00:03:25,817
-What's so funny?

54
00:03:25,851 --> 00:03:27,084
-Huh?

55
00:03:27,117 --> 00:03:31,017
Oh, uh, I was just
reading the funny pages.

56
00:03:31,051 --> 00:03:32,117
They kill me.

57
00:03:32,151 --> 00:03:34,451
[laughing]

58
00:03:34,484 --> 00:03:35,951
-Wait a minute.

59
00:03:35,984 --> 00:03:37,517
I've seen these guys before.

60
00:03:37,551 --> 00:03:38,151
-What guys?

61
00:03:47,351 --> 00:03:48,951
-Hey, yeah, you're right.

62
00:03:48,984 --> 00:03:50,651
I'm surprised you remember them.

63
00:03:50,684 --> 00:03:53,284
-Most people would.

64
00:03:53,317 --> 00:03:56,051
-Yeah, well, when you've busted
as many bad guys as I have,

65
00:03:56,084 --> 00:03:57,817
they all start to
blend together.

66
00:03:57,851 --> 00:04:01,817
-Yeah, or your memories going.

67
00:04:01,851 --> 00:04:05,351
KOTETSU: Says here
they were burned alive.

68
00:04:05,384 --> 00:04:07,384
-Gee, what a shame.

69
00:04:07,417 --> 00:04:08,651
-That's all you can say?

70
00:04:08,684 --> 00:04:10,384
-What else is there?

71
00:04:10,417 --> 00:04:13,184
-That's a hell of an attitude.

72
00:04:13,217 --> 00:04:14,151
Three men died.

73
00:04:14,184 --> 00:04:15,584
It doesn't matter who they are.

74
00:04:18,617 --> 00:04:21,551
I thought it was our job
to save people's lives.

75
00:04:21,584 --> 00:04:23,184
That's what a hero does.

76
00:04:23,217 --> 00:04:26,517
-Save the sermons for
someone who wants to listen.

77
00:04:26,551 --> 00:04:27,117
MR. LLOYDS: No.

78
00:04:27,151 --> 00:04:28,617
No problem at all.

79
00:04:28,651 --> 00:04:30,651
I'll have Wild Tiger
head over right way.

80
00:04:30,684 --> 00:04:31,684
-Hm.

81
00:04:31,717 --> 00:04:32,184
-No.

82
00:04:32,217 --> 00:04:33,284
Sorry.

83
00:04:33,317 --> 00:04:35,417
I'm afraid Barnaby's
tied up at the moment.

84
00:04:35,451 --> 00:04:38,617
You'll have to make
do with Wild Tiger.

85
00:04:38,651 --> 00:04:39,784
Yes, yes.

86
00:04:39,817 --> 00:04:41,051
He's quite resilient.

87
00:04:41,084 --> 00:04:45,084
-Mr. Lloyds, what's going on?

88
00:04:45,117 --> 00:04:47,551
[screaming]

89
00:04:55,651 --> 00:04:57,584
-Make the flame hotter.

90
00:04:57,617 --> 00:04:58,484
-If you insist.

91
00:05:02,351 --> 00:05:03,117
-No.

92
00:05:03,151 --> 00:05:04,051
We're still not there yet.

93
00:05:04,084 --> 00:05:06,217
It should be
hotter, much hotter.

94
00:05:06,251 --> 00:05:07,184
-What a sadist.

95
00:05:17,217 --> 00:05:20,117
-He's going to melt the
whole prison in a minute.

96
00:05:20,151 --> 00:05:20,784
-All right.

97
00:05:20,817 --> 00:05:21,384
That's enough.

98
00:05:21,417 --> 00:05:22,384
-Whatever you say.

99
00:05:31,484 --> 00:05:32,284
-[gasp] Water.

100
00:05:37,384 --> 00:05:38,051
-Hm.

101
00:05:38,084 --> 00:05:39,584
Too hot for you, honey.

102
00:05:39,617 --> 00:05:40,551
-Hey, man.

103
00:05:40,584 --> 00:05:42,151
Did you have to
lay it on so heavy?

104
00:05:42,184 --> 00:05:43,517
-Excuse me.

105
00:05:43,551 --> 00:05:45,817
I'm just trying to clear
myself of a murder charge.

106
00:05:45,851 --> 00:05:46,451
That's all.

107
00:05:46,484 --> 00:05:47,884
-How's it look?

108
00:05:47,917 --> 00:05:50,817
-Still don't have enough data.

109
00:05:50,851 --> 00:05:51,417
-All right.

110
00:05:51,451 --> 00:05:53,117
One more time.

111
00:05:53,151 --> 00:05:54,784
-One more time?

112
00:05:54,817 --> 00:05:56,617
-It's that or Fire
Emblem will have

113
00:05:56,651 --> 00:05:58,584
to be suspended from the show.

114
00:05:58,617 --> 00:06:00,684
-And you really think
all this will clear him

115
00:06:00,717 --> 00:06:02,117
of any suspicion?

116
00:06:02,151 --> 00:06:04,851
-It might see if we can reenact
the events of last night

117
00:06:04,884 --> 00:06:06,384
and then compare the data.

118
00:06:06,417 --> 00:06:08,484
-And my word's not
good enough for you?

119
00:06:08,517 --> 00:06:09,451
Hmph.

120
00:06:09,484 --> 00:06:10,684
TECHNICIAN: There's
nothing we know

121
00:06:10,717 --> 00:06:13,051
that could have produced
flames of such intensity.

122
00:06:13,084 --> 00:06:15,117
So it's natural to
suspect that whoever

123
00:06:15,151 --> 00:06:18,784
produced them wasn't a
normal human but a NEXT.

124
00:06:18,817 --> 00:06:21,317
-Yes, somebody a lot
like you in fact.

125
00:06:21,351 --> 00:06:23,184
-I am really not enjoying this.

126
00:06:23,217 --> 00:06:25,851
-Well, I'm not a big
fan of it either.

127
00:06:25,884 --> 00:06:28,217
Why do I have to be
put through this?

128
00:06:28,251 --> 00:06:30,084
Can't you just use a
dummy or something?

129
00:06:33,884 --> 00:06:36,251
[whispering]

130
00:06:36,284 --> 00:06:36,851
-Say what?

131
00:06:51,451 --> 00:06:53,817
-Glad you're amused.

132
00:06:53,851 --> 00:06:55,451
-Oh, so you're an opera fan.

133
00:06:55,484 --> 00:06:56,651
Really?

134
00:06:56,684 --> 00:06:58,817
-Yes, that's something I
picked up from my parents.

135
00:06:58,851 --> 00:07:01,317
-Oh, it's sweet the way
you talk about them.

136
00:07:01,351 --> 00:07:03,584
You must have loved
them very much.

137
00:07:03,617 --> 00:07:06,051
Now, do you have any
particular dislikes?

138
00:07:09,817 --> 00:07:13,417
Are there things you don't like?

139
00:07:13,451 --> 00:07:14,217
-Flames.

140
00:07:14,251 --> 00:07:15,351
I don't like fire.

141
00:07:21,851 --> 00:07:23,317
INTERVIEWER: Are you OK?

142
00:07:23,351 --> 00:07:25,117
Can we keep going?

143
00:07:25,151 --> 00:07:26,517
-Sure.

144
00:07:26,551 --> 00:07:28,917
INTERVIEWER: So what's your
favorite part of that outfit?

145
00:07:33,417 --> 00:07:33,884
-The belt.

146
00:07:36,784 --> 00:07:38,217
-Not enough data.

147
00:07:38,251 --> 00:07:39,551
Unbelievable.

148
00:07:39,584 --> 00:07:41,917
How much data do they need?

149
00:07:41,951 --> 00:07:44,417
And meanwhile, I'm
suspended from Hero TV.

150
00:07:44,451 --> 00:07:45,851
-Same time tomorrow.

151
00:07:45,884 --> 00:07:46,451
You too.

152
00:07:46,484 --> 00:07:47,817
-Huh.

153
00:07:47,851 --> 00:07:50,051
-We continue the tests till
we get to the bottom of this.

154
00:07:50,084 --> 00:07:50,717
-Ugh.

155
00:07:50,751 --> 00:07:51,817
You gotta be kidding me.

156
00:07:51,851 --> 00:07:53,684
-The sooner we clear
his name, the sooner

157
00:07:53,717 --> 00:07:55,251
we get him back on the show.

158
00:07:55,284 --> 00:07:56,217
Understand?

159
00:07:56,251 --> 00:07:58,517
-But what do you need me for?

160
00:07:58,551 --> 00:08:00,484
-Maybe we'll just hand
you over to the cops.

161
00:08:00,517 --> 00:08:01,751
How's that?

162
00:08:01,784 --> 00:08:03,684
-I almost think you'd do that.

163
00:08:03,717 --> 00:08:07,684
-So do you think they're right
in that a NEXT is behind it?

164
00:08:07,717 --> 00:08:10,417
Oh, It's scary to think that
there's someone out there

165
00:08:10,451 --> 00:08:12,551
with even more
sizzle than I have.

166
00:08:12,584 --> 00:08:14,384
[cheering]

167
00:08:21,884 --> 00:08:22,684
PRISON GUARD: Quick.

168
00:08:22,717 --> 00:08:24,151
We've got trouble in the yard.

169
00:08:30,651 --> 00:08:31,117
-Get back.

170
00:08:33,651 --> 00:08:34,451
I got you.

171
00:08:34,484 --> 00:08:35,251
I got you.

172
00:08:35,284 --> 00:08:37,751
Hang in there, buddy.

173
00:08:37,784 --> 00:08:41,384
Hey, hey, hey.

174
00:08:41,417 --> 00:08:43,251
Come on, buddy.

175
00:08:43,284 --> 00:08:44,551
No.

176
00:08:44,584 --> 00:08:45,051
No.

177
00:08:48,884 --> 00:08:51,317
-So tell me, what
did you guys see?

178
00:08:51,351 --> 00:08:52,751
-I don't know.

179
00:08:52,784 --> 00:08:55,817
It all went down so fast.

180
00:08:55,851 --> 00:08:57,651
-Anybody see what happened here?

181
00:09:21,051 --> 00:09:22,114
-Damn

182
00:09:30,751 --> 00:09:31,684
-Nope.

183
00:09:31,717 --> 00:09:33,551
I've never seen
anything like that.

184
00:09:33,584 --> 00:09:35,917
-And you've never heard
the name Ouroboros?

185
00:09:35,951 --> 00:09:36,584
-Uh-uh.

186
00:09:36,617 --> 00:09:37,151
Sorry.

187
00:09:37,184 --> 00:09:37,651
-OK.

188
00:09:37,684 --> 00:09:38,151
Thanks.

189
00:09:48,851 --> 00:09:50,117
-This symbol.

190
00:09:50,151 --> 00:09:52,551
Have you ever seen
one like it anywhere?

191
00:09:52,584 --> 00:09:54,651
-Dear me, I'm afraid not.

192
00:09:54,684 --> 00:09:55,151
No.

193
00:10:00,284 --> 00:10:01,384
-So you're positive?

194
00:10:01,417 --> 00:10:03,284
You're sure it doesn't
mean anything to you?

195
00:10:06,751 --> 00:10:09,651
-Sorry.

196
00:10:09,684 --> 00:10:10,951
-I finally found you.

197
00:10:10,984 --> 00:10:12,317
I'm not letting you get away.

198
00:10:12,351 --> 00:10:13,651
-Hey, get back, young man.

199
00:10:13,684 --> 00:10:15,617
-Not until he tells me
what those symbols mean.

200
00:10:15,651 --> 00:10:16,151
You know.

201
00:10:16,184 --> 00:10:17,151
Please tell me.

202
00:10:20,151 --> 00:10:20,651
-Ouroboros.

203
00:10:30,251 --> 00:10:32,784
AGNES (ON PHONE): Well, at least
this second attack clears you

204
00:10:32,817 --> 00:10:34,517
of any suspicion.

205
00:10:34,551 --> 00:10:36,684
-So they're sure it's
the same perp who

206
00:10:36,717 --> 00:10:37,717
fried the three others.

207
00:10:37,751 --> 00:10:38,951
AGNES (ON PHONE): Same method.

208
00:10:38,984 --> 00:10:39,917
Same location.

209
00:10:39,951 --> 00:10:41,417
Who else could it be?

210
00:10:41,451 --> 00:10:41,892
-Hm.

211
00:10:56,058 --> 00:10:58,758
KOTETSU: Hey, can you pull
over and let me off here?

212
00:10:58,792 --> 00:10:59,792
NATHAN: Really?

213
00:10:59,825 --> 00:11:01,825
But we're not even
close to your place.

214
00:11:01,858 --> 00:11:04,558
KOTETSU: Yeah, I know, but
I feel like taking a walk.

215
00:11:04,592 --> 00:11:05,625
Thanks.

216
00:11:05,658 --> 00:11:07,025
NATHAN: You going to
be all right, honey?

217
00:11:07,058 --> 00:11:07,758
KOTETSU: Sure.

218
00:11:07,792 --> 00:11:08,358
I'll be fine.

219
00:11:15,325 --> 00:11:16,425
-Say there.

220
00:11:16,458 --> 00:11:18,392
You sure you don't want
some company tonight?

221
00:11:18,425 --> 00:11:19,425
-Huh?

222
00:11:19,458 --> 00:11:21,058
NATHAN: A warm body
to snuggle up to?

223
00:11:21,092 --> 00:11:22,125
Hm?

224
00:11:22,158 --> 00:11:24,525
-Thanks, but you're
not exactly my type.

225
00:11:24,558 --> 00:11:25,858
You're too tall.

226
00:11:25,892 --> 00:11:27,058
NATHAN: Well, fine then.

227
00:11:27,092 --> 00:11:29,058
Your loss.

228
00:11:29,092 --> 00:11:29,758
[car horn honks]

229
00:11:29,792 --> 00:11:33,192
[opera music playing]

230
00:12:22,525 --> 00:12:23,758
-It's no good.

231
00:12:23,792 --> 00:12:24,858
I can't remember.

232
00:12:31,887 --> 00:12:33,520
-Mr. Saito, come in.

233
00:12:33,553 --> 00:12:36,487
Where's that damn suit
when I really need it?

234
00:12:36,520 --> 00:12:37,787
Why the hell doesn't he answer?

235
00:12:37,820 --> 00:12:38,287
Mr. Saito!

236
00:12:45,487 --> 00:12:46,453
Mr. Saito!

237
00:12:46,487 --> 00:12:47,787
BARNABY (ON PHONE): No, it's me.

238
00:12:47,820 --> 00:12:49,053
-Huh?

239
00:12:49,087 --> 00:12:51,120
-I don't appreciate you
messing around with my phone.

240
00:12:51,153 --> 00:12:52,320
KOTETSU (ON PHONE): What?

241
00:12:52,353 --> 00:12:54,053
-Don't ever do it again, OK.

242
00:12:54,087 --> 00:12:54,920
It's not funny.

243
00:12:54,953 --> 00:12:56,320
Goodbye.

244
00:12:56,353 --> 00:12:57,287
-Hey, wait!

245
00:12:57,320 --> 00:12:58,653
Wait!

246
00:12:58,687 --> 00:13:00,187
-Skip the apologies.

247
00:13:00,220 --> 00:13:01,787
KOTETSU (ON PHONE):
Who's apologizing.

248
00:13:01,820 --> 00:13:04,553
I'm under attack by
some giant robot thingy.

249
00:13:04,587 --> 00:13:05,553
-Yeah right.

250
00:13:05,587 --> 00:13:06,028
KOTETSU (ON PHONE): It's true.

251
00:13:06,061 --> 00:13:06,794
Dammit.

252
00:13:06,828 --> 00:13:07,594
And I don't have my suit.

253
00:13:07,628 --> 00:13:08,894
I really need--

254
00:13:08,928 --> 00:13:10,794
-Look I'm not falling for
any more of your pranks, OK.

255
00:13:10,828 --> 00:13:11,628
Bye.

256
00:13:11,661 --> 00:13:12,728
-Wait!

257
00:13:12,761 --> 00:13:14,228
Bunny!

258
00:13:14,261 --> 00:13:15,228
Bunny?

259
00:13:15,261 --> 00:13:18,194
Ah, crap.

260
00:13:18,228 --> 00:13:21,194
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

261
00:13:21,228 --> 00:13:21,661
Ah!

262
00:13:28,194 --> 00:13:28,728
OK.

263
00:13:28,761 --> 00:13:29,428
That does it.

264
00:13:36,828 --> 00:13:37,794
See ya.

265
00:13:37,828 --> 00:13:38,328
-Huh?

266
00:13:41,361 --> 00:13:42,694
Whoa!

267
00:13:42,728 --> 00:13:43,594
-Hey, wait.

268
00:13:43,628 --> 00:13:44,094
Hold on.

269
00:13:44,128 --> 00:13:44,594
Come back.

270
00:13:48,394 --> 00:13:51,128
-Well, well, you changed
your mind about my offer?

271
00:13:51,161 --> 00:13:52,461
-Don't flatter yourself.

272
00:13:52,494 --> 00:13:53,628
Take a look back there.

273
00:13:56,894 --> 00:13:57,961
-What in the world?

274
00:14:02,828 --> 00:14:04,728
-Hey, what the
hell are you doing?

275
00:14:04,761 --> 00:14:05,794
This is my car.

276
00:14:05,828 --> 00:14:06,394
-Go on.

277
00:14:06,428 --> 00:14:07,494
Use your powers.

278
00:14:07,528 --> 00:14:09,428
Fry that bastard.

279
00:14:09,461 --> 00:14:11,428
-You have powers too, don't you?

280
00:14:11,461 --> 00:14:13,361
-Yeah, I know, but I
don't want to waste them.

281
00:14:13,394 --> 00:14:16,061
I may need them later.

282
00:14:16,094 --> 00:14:18,761
The whole point of having
powers is to save people.

283
00:14:18,794 --> 00:14:19,461
-Yes.

284
00:14:19,494 --> 00:14:20,794
So use yours to save me.

285
00:14:28,728 --> 00:14:30,428
Out of ammo?

286
00:14:30,461 --> 00:14:31,494
-Let's find out.

287
00:14:37,928 --> 00:14:38,461
Nope.

288
00:14:38,494 --> 00:14:40,361
Definitely not.

289
00:14:40,394 --> 00:14:42,761
-Well, I guess I have no choice.

290
00:14:42,794 --> 00:14:43,261
Fire.

291
00:14:47,228 --> 00:14:48,994
You've got to be kidding.

292
00:14:49,028 --> 00:14:52,361
-Hit the deck.

293
00:14:52,394 --> 00:14:54,494
-Whatever that thing is,
it just snuffed my flames

294
00:14:54,528 --> 00:14:55,461
like they were nothing.

295
00:14:58,128 --> 00:15:01,028
-So maybe we found the guy
responsible for the murders.

296
00:15:01,061 --> 00:15:02,594
-Could be.

297
00:15:02,628 --> 00:15:04,994
One way to find out.

298
00:15:05,028 --> 00:15:08,728
Let's get him out
of that contraption.

299
00:15:08,761 --> 00:15:10,528
-He's coming.

300
00:15:10,561 --> 00:15:12,094
-I'll try and distract him.

301
00:15:12,128 --> 00:15:13,294
-Huh?

302
00:15:13,328 --> 00:15:16,028
-I'll draw his fire, while
you find his weak spot.

303
00:15:16,061 --> 00:15:16,861
-Uh, OK.

304
00:15:20,694 --> 00:15:21,194
-Get going.

305
00:15:39,628 --> 00:15:42,594
-Ooh, you are so butch.

306
00:15:42,628 --> 00:15:43,594
-All right.

307
00:15:43,628 --> 00:15:47,394
Come on out of
there, you-- hold on.

308
00:15:47,428 --> 00:15:48,894
I know you.

309
00:15:48,928 --> 00:15:51,328
[horn honks]

310
00:15:51,361 --> 00:15:52,294
-Reinforcements.

311
00:15:52,328 --> 00:15:54,728
[sirens]

312
00:15:57,694 --> 00:15:59,028
-Well, what do you know?

313
00:16:04,461 --> 00:16:12,794
What the-- I was wondering
if you were going to show up.

314
00:16:12,828 --> 00:16:14,761
Nice of you to fit me
into your schedule.

315
00:16:14,794 --> 00:16:15,728
-Don't get too excited.

316
00:16:15,761 --> 00:16:17,794
I didn't come here
for your sake.

317
00:16:17,828 --> 00:16:18,828
-I know.

318
00:16:18,861 --> 00:16:20,328
It was for my sake
you came, wasn't it?

319
00:16:20,361 --> 00:16:21,561
-Nope.

320
00:16:21,594 --> 00:16:23,328
Honestly, I didn't even
know you were here.

321
00:16:23,361 --> 00:16:24,994
-Oh.

322
00:16:25,028 --> 00:16:26,528
-So where's the culprit?

323
00:16:26,561 --> 00:16:28,128
-He got away.

324
00:16:28,161 --> 00:16:28,628
-Uh-uh.

325
00:16:28,661 --> 00:16:29,561
-Damn.

326
00:16:29,594 --> 00:16:30,961
I was hoping to
earn some points.

327
00:16:30,994 --> 00:16:34,861
-Gee, I'm real sorry about that.

328
00:16:34,894 --> 00:16:35,761
-What?

329
00:16:35,794 --> 00:16:37,628
You've seen that man before?

330
00:16:37,661 --> 00:16:39,061
-Yeah, I have.

331
00:16:39,094 --> 00:16:40,094
NATHAN: When?

332
00:16:40,128 --> 00:16:40,828
Where?

333
00:16:40,861 --> 00:16:43,061
-I'm trying to remember.

334
00:16:43,094 --> 00:16:44,861
I met him somewhere.

335
00:16:44,894 --> 00:16:46,194
-We're wasting our time here.

336
00:16:46,228 --> 00:16:47,194
It's hopeless.

337
00:16:47,228 --> 00:16:48,028
-Huh?

338
00:16:48,061 --> 00:16:49,628
-The old man's memory is going.

339
00:16:49,661 --> 00:16:51,128
He can't even remember faces.

340
00:16:51,161 --> 00:16:52,561
-Will you shut up?

341
00:16:52,594 --> 00:16:54,994
-You know I think
Handsome has a point.

342
00:16:55,028 --> 00:16:56,794
You're not much help, are you?

343
00:16:56,828 --> 00:16:58,594
In fact, come to
think of it, I don't

344
00:16:58,628 --> 00:17:00,128
know how he puts up with you.

345
00:17:00,161 --> 00:17:01,728
-Weren't you the
one who just offered

346
00:17:01,761 --> 00:17:04,828
to spend the night
snuggling with me?

347
00:17:04,861 --> 00:17:05,928
-He's crazy.

348
00:17:05,961 --> 00:17:06,894
I swear to you.

349
00:17:06,928 --> 00:17:09,361
There's nothing
going on between us.

350
00:17:09,394 --> 00:17:11,194
Nothing.

351
00:17:11,228 --> 00:17:13,894
-Like I said, this
is a waste of time.

352
00:17:13,928 --> 00:17:14,761
I'm leaving.

353
00:17:14,794 --> 00:17:15,294
-Good.

354
00:17:15,328 --> 00:17:15,861
-Wait.

355
00:17:15,894 --> 00:17:19,194
I'm coming with.

356
00:17:19,228 --> 00:17:20,561
[whispering]

357
00:17:20,594 --> 00:17:21,128
-Say what?

358
00:17:23,961 --> 00:17:24,961
-That's right.

359
00:17:24,994 --> 00:17:26,528
Where the hell were you?

360
00:17:26,561 --> 00:17:27,961
I almost got myself killed.

361
00:17:30,728 --> 00:17:31,194
-Huh?

362
00:17:40,194 --> 00:17:41,528
-You poor guy.

363
00:17:41,561 --> 00:17:44,161
What the hell is going on with
all the elevators in this town

364
00:17:44,194 --> 00:17:44,661
anyway?

365
00:17:47,294 --> 00:17:48,794
-I just fixed it.

366
00:17:48,828 --> 00:17:51,561
-Thank you, Mr. Saito.

367
00:17:51,594 --> 00:17:54,894
I just remembered where
I've seen that guy.

368
00:17:54,928 --> 00:17:56,228
-Oh.

369
00:17:56,261 --> 00:17:58,261
-He's the worker who was coming
out of the elevator right

370
00:17:58,294 --> 00:18:00,794
before the bomb scare.

371
00:18:00,828 --> 00:18:01,861
-You lost me.

372
00:18:01,894 --> 00:18:05,128
-And he came after
you, because--

373
00:18:05,161 --> 00:18:05,994
-Mhm.

374
00:18:06,028 --> 00:18:06,761
Let's go.

375
00:18:06,794 --> 00:18:07,661
-Where?

376
00:18:07,694 --> 00:18:09,028
What?

377
00:18:09,061 --> 00:18:12,961
I can't stand being
kept in the dark.

378
00:18:12,994 --> 00:18:14,294
-Come on, Bunny.

379
00:18:14,328 --> 00:18:15,661
Would you step on it?

380
00:18:15,694 --> 00:18:18,061
-What use are you going to be
anyway without your powers?

381
00:18:18,094 --> 00:18:20,361
You've got an hour before
you get them back, don't you?

382
00:18:20,394 --> 00:18:21,794
-Ah, who cares about that?

383
00:18:21,828 --> 00:18:22,728
Look.

384
00:18:22,761 --> 00:18:23,661
I'm going to nail
this creep, if I

385
00:18:23,694 --> 00:18:24,961
have to do it with
my bare hands.

386
00:18:24,994 --> 00:18:27,428
-Sorry to interrupt
this macho banter,

387
00:18:27,461 --> 00:18:29,828
but will someone tell
me what is going on?

388
00:18:29,861 --> 00:18:32,728
-The perp in question is trying
to silence any witnesses who

389
00:18:32,761 --> 00:18:34,828
saw him at the scene
of the bomb scare.

390
00:18:34,861 --> 00:18:35,928
-Ah.

391
00:18:35,961 --> 00:18:36,694
Were there others?

392
00:18:36,728 --> 00:18:38,294
Who else was there?

393
00:18:38,328 --> 00:18:42,194
-Agnes and the camera man.

394
00:18:42,228 --> 00:18:44,828
-All right, but I
need that final edit

395
00:18:44,861 --> 00:18:46,828
on my desk first
thing in the morning.

396
00:18:46,861 --> 00:18:47,394
Got it?

397
00:18:58,094 --> 00:18:59,561
-What the hell?

398
00:18:59,594 --> 00:19:00,561
What are you doing?

399
00:19:10,961 --> 00:19:12,261
-You all right?

400
00:19:12,294 --> 00:19:12,761
-Barnaby.

401
00:19:16,928 --> 00:19:19,661
-Looks like we got
here just in time.

402
00:19:19,694 --> 00:19:21,261
-You again.

403
00:19:21,294 --> 00:19:22,828
-Safe and sound.

404
00:19:22,861 --> 00:19:24,261
-Just who is this guy?

405
00:19:24,294 --> 00:19:25,361
-Later, honey.

406
00:19:25,394 --> 00:19:27,028
Right now, we've got
to get you out of here.

407
00:19:27,061 --> 00:19:28,461
-I'll finish all of you.

408
00:19:46,061 --> 00:19:47,094
-What's wrong?

409
00:19:47,128 --> 00:19:48,628
That all you've got?

410
00:19:48,661 --> 00:19:49,794
-Nice work, Handsome.

411
00:19:49,828 --> 00:19:52,394
-Hey, how come you
always get the spotlight?

412
00:19:52,428 --> 00:19:53,228
-Be my guest.

413
00:19:53,261 --> 00:19:54,594
There aren't any
points involved.

414
00:19:54,628 --> 00:19:55,428
-Huh?

415
00:19:55,461 --> 00:19:58,828
Oh, OK.

416
00:19:58,861 --> 00:20:02,161
The party's over,
you lowlife scumbag.

417
00:20:02,194 --> 00:20:03,994
We're taking you in.

418
00:20:04,028 --> 00:20:06,728
-Then stop showing off and
take me in, you jackass.

419
00:20:12,228 --> 00:20:14,028
BARNABY (VOICEOVER): Ouroburos.

420
00:20:14,061 --> 00:20:16,761
-You made a big mistake
tangling with me, punk.

421
00:20:16,794 --> 00:20:18,594
I'm gonna-- hey,
what are you doing?

422
00:20:18,628 --> 00:20:20,694
You said I could handle this.

423
00:20:20,728 --> 00:20:22,961
-That tattoo on your neck.

424
00:20:22,994 --> 00:20:25,061
It's an Ouroburos, isn't it?

425
00:20:25,094 --> 00:20:26,694
What is it?

426
00:20:26,728 --> 00:20:27,894
Some kind of crime syndicate?

427
00:20:31,194 --> 00:20:35,228
-Where's the man who wears
that mark on his hand?

428
00:20:35,261 --> 00:20:35,728
Answer me.

429
00:20:44,794 --> 00:20:45,561
-Hey, hey, wait.

430
00:20:45,594 --> 00:20:46,594
What are you going to do?

431
00:20:46,628 --> 00:20:47,494
-Out of my way.

432
00:20:47,528 --> 00:20:48,061
-All right.

433
00:20:48,094 --> 00:20:49,294
Just calm down.

434
00:20:49,328 --> 00:20:50,061
What's eating you?

435
00:20:50,094 --> 00:20:51,461
-Stay out of it.

436
00:20:51,494 --> 00:20:52,961
-They're at it again.

437
00:20:52,994 --> 00:20:56,828
Honestly, you're like
an old married couple.

438
00:20:59,661 --> 00:21:01,994
-Take off those masks and
put your hands in the air.

439
00:21:07,461 --> 00:21:08,561
I'll blow her head off.

440
00:21:08,594 --> 00:21:10,494
I swear.

441
00:21:10,528 --> 00:21:11,861
-OK.

442
00:21:11,894 --> 00:21:14,294
OK.

443
00:21:14,328 --> 00:21:15,994
-The other guy too.

444
00:21:16,028 --> 00:21:17,961
Now!

445
00:21:17,994 --> 00:21:18,928
-Hey.

446
00:21:18,961 --> 00:21:19,928
-Better do it.

447
00:21:24,328 --> 00:21:25,661
-There we go.

448
00:21:25,694 --> 00:21:27,861
-What's your game anyway?

449
00:21:27,894 --> 00:21:30,461
Why'd you kill those
guys in the prison cell?

450
00:21:30,494 --> 00:21:32,328
How the hell do they
fit into all this?

451
00:21:32,361 --> 00:21:33,161
-What?

452
00:21:33,194 --> 00:21:35,094
-And the one this morning?

453
00:21:35,128 --> 00:21:36,161
Why?

454
00:21:36,194 --> 00:21:37,394
-I don't know what
you're talking about?

455
00:21:37,428 --> 00:21:38,928
-Don't play dumb with me.

456
00:21:38,961 --> 00:21:39,594
Come on.

457
00:21:39,628 --> 00:21:41,394
-I said I don't know.

458
00:21:41,428 --> 00:21:43,094
I'm going to do you first.

459
00:21:54,528 --> 00:21:55,994
-What on earth was that?

460
00:21:59,461 --> 00:22:00,494
-Is it human?

461
00:22:12,428 --> 00:22:15,928
[screaming]

462
00:22:41,329 --> 00:22:44,795
[theme music]

463
00:24:11,386 --> 00:24:14,219
KOTETSU: Hey, Kotetsu here,
the member of Tiger and Bunny

464
00:24:14,253 --> 00:24:16,386
who prefers to bite
into his candy.

465
00:24:16,419 --> 00:24:17,853
Oh, so it's you again.

466
00:24:17,886 --> 00:24:19,519
Who are you anyway?

467
00:24:19,553 --> 00:24:20,053
OK.

468
00:24:20,053 --> 00:24:21,186
Fine.

469
00:24:21,186 --> 00:24:21,640
I guess I'll just have
find out the hard way.

470
00:24:21,640 --> 00:24:25,540
Next time on "Tiger & Bunny,"
"The Wolf Knows the Beast is--"

471
00:24:25,540 --> 00:24:26,100
wait.

